tirei daqui: https://www.kaggle.com/code/annastasy/predicting-students-grades

StudentID → Unique identifier for each student.
Age → Student age.
Gender → Student gender (0 = Female, 1 = Male).
Ethnicity → Ethnicity group/category represented numerically.
ParentalEducation → Parents’ education level (0–4, where higher values represent higher education levels).
StudyTimeWeekly → Average number of study hours per week.
Absences → Number of school absences.
Tutoring → Whether the student receives tutoring support (0 = No, 1 = Yes).
ParentalSupport → Level of parental support (0–4, from low to high support).
Extracurricular → Participation in extracurricular activities (0 = No, 1 = Yes).
Sports → Participation in sports activities (0 = No, 1 = Yes).
Music → Participation in music-related activities (0 = No, 1 = Yes).
Volunteering → Participation in volunteering activities (0 = No, 1 = Yes).
GPA → Grade Point Average, representing the student’s academic performance.
GradeClass → Final predicted/performance class (0–4, where lower values usually represent better academic performance).



average="weighted"-> pondera pelo tamanho das classes

precision- Das previsões que fiz para esta classe, quantas estavam certas?
recall- De todos os exemplos reais desta classe, quantos o modelo encontrou?
f1_score = 2 * (precison * recall / (precision + recall))
support- Número de amostras reais dessa classe no y_test